title: Kylie Jenner covers her face with sunglasses while leaving skin care clinic
title_page: Kylie Jenner covers her face with sunglasses while leaving skin care clinic | Daily Mail Online
text:
She's certainly not known for having a shy and retiring nature.
But Kylie Jenner covered her face with a pair of oversized sunglasses on Thursday as she left a skincare clinic in Beverly Hills - even though it was dark outside.
However the 18-year-old couldn't resist showing off her cleavage and flat midriff in her casual ensemble.
Scroll down for video
On the go: Kylie Jenner was spotted leaving Epione, a skin care center, while wearing a low cut black tank and fitted sweats
The Keeping Up With The Kardashians star didn't crack a smile as she left the office, rocking a slightly sheer black top and fitted grey bottoms with a cream colored waistband.
Her light colored sweats featured a zipper detail on the sides of her hips as well the hemline.
She stayed warm in a cuffed shiny black bomber jacket while pounding the pavement in grey Yeezy 350 Boost sneakers.
Kylie shielded her makeup free face with the large shades and pulled her raven hued locks back into a casual low bun.
Casual chic: The 18-year-old showed off her cleavage and flat midriff in her casual ensemble on Thursday in Beverly Hills
The brunette beauty,who wore her signature Cartier bracelets as well as a large golden watch, sported neutral hued polish on her nails.
Earlier in the day, the teen shared a photo to her 49.4 million Instagram followers of her outfit without her jacket.
In a video on her website, thekyliejenner.com, the teen revealed she wanted time to get to know herself, saying: 'I feel like I have been in a relationship for six years. I have just gone from one person to the next.'
Kylie added: 'I was dating someone for like, three years, 14, 15, 16, and a little bit of 17. I went into another relationship, 17, 18. I feel like I really need to find myself.'
Serious: The Keeping Up With The Kardashians star didn't crack a smile as she left the office, rocking a slightly sheer black top and fitted grey leggings with a cream colored waistband

She continued: 'And have like a relationship with myself. Because I don't know what it feels like to be by myself. I feel like you have to love yourself before you can love anybody else.'
The teenager has had a drama filled week.
It was revealed this week that her brother, Rob Kardashian, is not only dating Blac Chyna, but that he's also moved in with her.
